30/08/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia -- A group of Serbian skinheads wearing Nazi regalia attacked two Israelis at a concert Sunday (27 August). Witnesses say the young men shouted racial slurs and beat Yariv Avram and Bojana Petkovic. They say police officers guarding the concert in a Belgrade park did not intervene. Serbian Jewish community leaders say hate crimes have grown more common in recent years.
In other news, the Serbian Supreme Court has upheld the convictions of four people sentenced to a total of 21 years in prison for human trafficking. The three men and a woman organised a ring that smuggled prostitutes into Western Europe. (UPI, IsraelNN.com - 29/08/06)
